FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE, BOVINE - COLOMBIA: OIE
******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 11 Mar 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Office International des Epizooties(OIE), Disease
Information, Vol. 18- No. 10 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/a_current.htm#Sec4>

Foot and mouth disease in Colombia
See also: 7 Jan 2005, 17 Sep 2004, 3 Sep 2004, 27 Aug 2004, 13 Aug 2004
(Date of previous outbreak of foot and mouth disease in Colombia reported
to the OIE: August 2004).
Immediate notification report
Translation of information received on 10 Mar 2005 from Dr Juan Alcides
Santaella Guttierez, General Manager, Colombian Institute for Agriculture
and Livestock (ICA), Bogota:
Report date: 9 Mar 2005.
Reason for immediate notification: re-occurrence of a listed disease in a
country, zone/compartment following a report declaring the outbreak(s) ended.
Precise identification of agent: foot and mouth disease virus serotype A.
Date of first confirmation of the event: 7 Mar 2005.
Date of start of the event: 25 Feb 2005.
Clinical disease: yes.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Details of outbreak:
1st administrative division: Cundinamarca
Lower administrative division: Bogota
Type of epidemiological unit: farm
Name of the location: National University
Latitude/ Longitude: 4 deg 38 min 1 sec N 74 deg 5 min 21 sec W
Date of start of the outbreak: 25 Feb. 2005
Number of animals in the outbreak
susceptible/ cases /deaths /destroyed /slaughtered
Species bov 36 / 1 / 0 / 4 / 0
Species o/c 31 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Description of affected population:
Cattle of Normandy breed located in a University research unit in the urban
area of Bogota. These comprised 4 bovines less than 1 year old, 4 heifers
between 1 and 2 years old, cows over 2 years old and 3 bulls over 2 years
old. The affected bovine belonged to the group of heifers. This group was
separated from the other age groups.
Diagnosis:
Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Laboratory of Vesicular
Diseases, Bogota
Species examined: bovine
Diagnostic tests used:
- virus isolation in cell culture;
- complement fixation test;
- virus isolation in cell culture;
- complement fixation test;
- PCR(1).
Date: 7 Mar 2005
Results: positive
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.
Control measures undertaken:
- partial stamping out;
- quarantine;
- movement control inside the country;
- disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s).
Treatment of affected animals: no.
Vaccination prohibited: no.
Other details/comments:
- The outbreak was confirmed in the endemic FMD zone of Colombia,
specifically in the Department of Cundinamarca. In this area no outbreaks
have been confirmed since September 2002 (29 months).
- A perifocal area of 10 km has been defined in which epidemiological
surveillance is being carried out, including clinical inspections of all
susceptible animals. A buffer zone of 25 km has been defined around this
outbreak in which surveillance actions have been intensified.
(1) PCR: polymerase chain reaction
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This is unfortunate, as the previous report indicates good progress was
being made in this area. Unfortunately, this is an all-too-common
occurrence in FMD eradication programs. Good luck in stamping this one
out. - Mod.PC]
